vors, the public, and policymakers. The group has the stated goal "to abolish the institution of prostitution while at the same time advocating for alternatives to trafficking and prostitution – including emotional and physical healthcare for women in prostitution."<ref name=2014PRE-website>{{cite web|title=Mission|url=http://prostitutionresearch.com/about/mission/|work=prostitutionresearch.com|accessdate=5 September 2014}}</ref>
The organization is sponsored by the San Francisco Women's Centers, Inc.<ref name=farleycv>[http://disability-abuse.com/txt/OnlineFacultyCVs/FarleyCV.txt "Melissa Farley: Curriculum Vitae"], 2004.</ref>
